Yellow capsicums are in big demand in hotels and supermarkets and they fetch higher prices compared to the red and green varieties. The green and red capsicums go for Sh5-Sh10 while the yellow capsicum goes for Sh20-Sh50.
There are two types of capsicums:
i) Sweet pepper/bell pepper (green, red and yellow in colour)ii) Hot pepper
Environmental requirements
Capsicums are warm-season crops and are highly susceptible to frost. The optimum temperature for growth and development is 21oC-24oC for sweet pepper and 21oC-29oC for hot pepper.



