}



Leaf miners
The larvae is the most destructive. It makes long-winding mines under the leaf epidermis. The infected leaves are blotchy. Control is by removing infected leaves 
Mites and whiteflies
They suck sap mostly from underside of the leaves and also transmit viruses. Controlled by insecticides or by use of yellow sticky traps.
Market
Locally, capsicums are sold in hotels, hospitals, institutions, directly to consumers in markets or by selling them to middlemen.
Value addition 
Value addition can be done on hot pepper by drying and grinding to get chilli powder, which can be mixed with other dry ingredients like coriander, garlic, ginger and salt.



