Benefits of growing capsicums
i) They mature in three months thus farmers can start getting income in a very short time.ii) They have market locally and abroad.iii) It’s a hardy crop.iv) Yellow capsicums fetch a higher market price than the green and red ones.
Nutritional benefits
i) They are rich in vitamins A, B and C.ii) They contain copper, zinc, potassium, manganese and selenium.iii) They can lower cholesterol levels in people who are obese.iv) They contain a substance called capsaicin which is anti-bacterial, anti-carcinogenic, analgesic and has anti-diabetic properties.



