****Milk spoilage
Why does milk get spoilt  the moment I try to boil it?
Cynthia Jeruto
Milk can coagulate on boiling due to salt imbalance attributed to the health of the animal (mastitis disease), stage of lactation (early or late) or type of feed given to the animal. High protein content in milk can also lead to coagulation, such as in colostrum.
Kevine Otieno,Department of Dairy, Food Science & Technology.
****Animal feed ingredients’ crude protein
Please advise: what is the digestible crude protein (DCP) of whole maize, maize germ, wheat bran, wheat pollard, cotton seed cake, sunflower cake, soya bean cake and fishmeal.
William
DCP is the actual amount of crude protein absorbed by an animal. Put differently, it is the protein in the feed minus the protein in the animal waste.
Looking at the feed ingredients you have listed, we have energy sources whole maize, maize germ, wheat bran and wheat pollard and plant protein sources cotton seedcake, sunflower cake, soybean cake as well as animal protein source fishmeal.
When making animal feeds, the nutrient composition of the feed ingredients is determined, followed by determining the nutrient requirement of the animal of interest like cattle, sheep, fish, pets, poultry and pigs to make feeds that meet their nutrient requirements using the same ingredients.



